00:00:21.450 --> 00:00:25.440
&gt;&gt; Well, I was very anxious and I called my doctor,

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:32.220
he was away. I called another doctor and he was away. And I

00:00:32.220 --> 00:00:38.630
called a friend who works at one of those local hospitals and I said this is the

00:00:38.630 --> 00:00:45.640
situation, what do you recommend I do? And she gave me the name of a doctor,

00:00:45.640 --> 00:00:50.650
and it was confirmed, by the time I had that information it was confirmed by

00:00:50.650 --> 00:00:55.680
the doctor who had returned. So I went to see a breast oncologist

00:00:55.680 --> 00:01:00.270
and, at a very large medical center

00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:05.580
and at the same time she scheduled me to see a genetic

00:01:05.580 --> 00:01:10.780
counselor. which is recommended, when you, when you get

00:01:10.780 --> 00:01:15.850
this information it's recommended that you speak to someone and see

00:01:15.850 --> 00:01:21.660
someone who understands the genetics so I did see this person in

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:29.530
the physician and the generic counselor on the same day and she was

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:35.210
gave me a very thorough exam and a very thorough explanation there was no rush.

00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:41.800
And I was advised, to consider, strongly

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:48.365
having my ovaries removed. And to have twice a year breast exam,

00:01:48.365 --> 00:01:54.805
and a one time a year breast MRI,

00:01:54.805 --> 00:02:00.910
and a breast mammogram. And I followed up, I've already followed up

00:02:00.910 --> 00:02:07.190
two times. I see her twice a year, and I've had the MRI and breast exam twice.

00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:09.509
&gt;&gt; Wow, you took a lot of action.

00:02:09.509 --> 00:02:11.020
&gt;&gt; I did.

00:02:11.020 --> 00:02:15.060
&gt;&gt; And this was all based on the advice and the the

