died when my mother was five. So we're talking about the 1920s and I was always

00:02:48.340 --> 00:02:53.540
told my grandmother died of stomach cancer and the genetic counts that brought

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:59.730
up the possibility that she had had ovarian cancer, of course we wouldn't know,

00:02:59.730 --> 00:03:05.230
this was the 1920s. And that was what we, would be heard, that she died

00:03:05.230 --> 00:03:09.390
of stomach cancer but it could have been ovarian cancer.

