00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:34.900
I discussed this, and it just seemed like it was the right thing to do. Of

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:40.050
course, I read a lot, and I had family

00:03:40.050 --> 00:03:45.020
members who had breast cancer, and ovarian cancer,

00:03:45.020 --> 00:03:50.280
and none of them were BRCA2 or any BRCA

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:55.690
for that matter. So, it wasn't as if I knew anybody that

00:03:55.690 --> 00:03:58.150
had this, was in this situation.

00:03:58.150 --> 00:04:01.350
&gt;&gt; if you had any advice to tell somebody who

00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:04.240
just found out they have a BRCA 1 or BRCA 2

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:06.580
mutation, is there anything you think it's important for them to

00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:10.150
know or any particular advice or message you would give them?

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:15.440
&gt;&gt; Well, if someone does inquire and finds out.

00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:20.740
I certainly think they should get genetic counselling. And see

00:04:20.740 --> 00:04:25.794
a physician who is a specialist, in breast

00:04:25.794 --> 00:04:31.490
oncology. Who is aware of the latest and greatest

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:36.070
research. we're fortunate to live in an area where

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:42.030
there are wonderful hospitals and research centers. And so I strongly

00:04:42.030 --> 00:04:46.890
advise people to take action and

00:04:46.890 --> 00:04:51.050
do what's best for them. I know age is a

00:04:51.050 --> 00:04:55.250
factor. If you find out you're in your 20s or 30s

00:04:55.250 --> 00:05:00.020
and you haven't started a family or had children yet, what's

00:05:00.020 --> 00:05:04.040
recommended might be entirely different than what was recommended for me.

00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:06.790
